#: admin/partials/faq.php:15
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:22
msgid "Does this plugin require BuddyPress?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:24
msgid "No. This plugin works standalone on any WordPress site. BuddyPress, WooCommerce, bbPress, Dokan, LearnDash, and PeepSo support is automatically enabled when those plugins are active."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:31
msgid "What happens if no redirect is configured?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:33
msgid "WordPress default behavior applies: admins go to the dashboard, other users go to the profile or home page."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:40
msgid "What is the redirect priority order?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:42
msgid "User Role redirect takes highest priority, followed by Integration Group Types (e.g. BuddyPress member types), then Global redirect, and finally WordPress default."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:49
msgid "Can I use role and BuddyPress member type redirects together?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:51
msgid "Yes! Role-based redirects take priority. If no role redirect is configured for a user, the plugin will check their BuddyPress member type, then fall back to global settings."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:58
msgid "Which integrations are supported?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:60
msgid "BuddyPress (Profile, Activity, Groups + Member Types), WooCommerce (My Account, Shop, Checkout, Orders), bbPress (Forums, User Profile), Dokan (Vendor Dashboard, Store Page), LearnDash (Dashboard, Courses), and PeepSo (Profile, Activity)."
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:67
msgid "Where do I ask for support?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:69
msgid "Please visit"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:69
msgid "Wbcom Designs"
msgstr ""

#: admin/partials/faq.php:69
msgid "for any query related to the plugin."
msgstr ""

